explanation: XOR produces a mask where each bit is 1 only where the corresponding bits of start and goal differ; counting those 1-bits gives the exact number of flips needed. Java’s Integer.bitCount uses a highly-optimized CPU instruction (POPCNT) for this count, making the solution constant-time and extremely energy-efficient.

